Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario, using modern MSTest 3.9+ attributes:

**1. Windows-only tests** — `[OSCondition]` (MSTest 3.10+)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void WindowsRegistry_ReadsValue()
{
    var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "Setting", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(value);
}
```

**2. Skip in CI** — `[CICondition]` (MSTest 3.10+)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void GpuRendering_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    var result = GpuRenderer.Render(scene);
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

**3. Flaky external API** — `[Retry]` (MSTest 3.9+)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(
        "Seattle", _testContext.CancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
}
```
Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies — not to mask race conditions or shared state bugs.

**4. Cleanup on failure** — `[TestCleanup]` or `IDisposable`
```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class FileProcessorTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public FileProcessorTests()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile_WritesExpectedContent()
    {
        FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        var content = File.ReadAllText(_tempFile);
        Assert.Contains("expected", content);
    }

    // Runs even if the test fails
    public void Dispose()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```
`[TestCleanup]`, `Dispose`, and `DisposeAsync` all run even when a test fails. Use `IDisposable` for simple resource cleanup; use `[TestCleanup]` if you need async cleanup or access to `TestContext`.

**Combined example:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
[Retry(2)]
[Timeout(5000)]
public async Task GpuRegistry_ReadsAndRenders()
{
    // Attributes compose — this test only runs on Windows,
    // outside CI, and retries up to 2 times on failure.
}
```

All of these require **MSTest 3.10+** (or 3.9+ for `[Retry]`). Make sure your project references at least that version.
